entries.femaleVariant: Anders Hellman. Hot-shot engineer. Worked for Arasaka.
Millisec.
Anders Hellman – need to track him down.
What was that about?
Even you lost people in action.
They knew the risks. All sorts of shit happens – to all sorts of people.
The girl – what was her gripe?
[Sit] Hope you found him.
[Take chip] Let's have a look.
All clear. Thanks.
Good luck.
That was the good news.
Can we talk?
No. This trouble, the net around me – you wove it.
Rogue? Wanted to talk.
Lemme be plain. Again. Solve your own problems, clean up your shit.
Do you know what, Rogue? Go fuck yourself.
You got Johnny killed.
Arasaka Tower - 'member? Who'd you lose back then? Johnny something...
entries.maleVariant: Arasaka Tower - 'member? Who'd you lose back then? Johnny somethin'…

entries.femaleVariant: Ah. You came prepped. 'Course.
Siddown.
What's the bad news?
Got this intel pretty fast.
Bad news is the extraction site. Look – Night City airspace, all this.
And here, we're too close to Kang Tao. We even give that AV a dirty look, their backup huscle'll be on us.
Know the right person?
What sort of gear'll I need?
What kind of gear are we talkin'?
Cruisin' speed of an AV like that's two hundred and fifty miles an hour. Ever tried to grab anything moving that fast?
It's not about firepower. There are ways. And people who know them. Or who can at least improvise on a theme.
Even tracking her'll be difficult. Plus, this model packs next-gen defenses.
Panam has to help me? Why?
Strange. Nomads usually keep clear of city folk.
Why's Panam gotta help me? I sense a catch. Pretty big one.
Occasionally, Panam moves merch for me. Last job... well, wasn't a good day for her.
She run into a hitch?
Complete bust, actually. Lost the goods and her ride. Panam'll do anything to get the load back. Means her dignity – I know her.
OK, guess I can try to help her. But if we don't know where to look, I mean…
entries.maleVariant: OK, guess I can try to help her. But if we don't know where to look, I mean--

entries.femaleVariant: We do. I do.
Wow. Gonna try to play me like Panam?
So tell me.
You know, but wouldn't tell Panam? Aim to play cat and mouse with me, too?
My aim is to know an opportunity when I see one. And then to seize it.
Say I told her everything. Whaddaya think she'd 'ave done? Grabbed her iron and gone on the warpath, that's what. Not hard to see how that coulda ended.
Fine. Lemme hear what you know.
Rocky Ridge, ghost town just outside Night City. Panam knows where.
You'll go there, get the merch back. Wheels, too.
Naturally, you'll call her first. Sendin' you her detes.
Queen of The Afterlife. Who woulda thunk…
Why don't ya ask her. Might still be around, sniveling in a corner.
Need your services. Gotta track a guy down.
Mhm?
A dead zone. I'll grab him there.
Hm. Can't be trusted if her clan banished her. Sorry, just not willin' to pay you for help like that.
Varies by clan, by the connections they have, the depth of the shit they're in.
Actually, she walked away. Said it was about the family, its future, nomad ideals, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah... I stopped listening a few words in.
Thought you preferred to know who you're dealing with.
I know enough. 'Sides, when someone starts spouting "ideals," it's prolly about something else. Power, usually.
Fortunately, not my biz, not yours. Panam's capable and stands to help you – that's all you need to know.
Mhm. No way to 'jack the transport without the NCPD picking up on it.
But... right here's Jackson Plains. Narrow corridor just outside the city and just out of Kang Tao's reach.
But you're right – Aldecaldos're rarely willing to do biz with the city.
Panam's got a different take?
Yep. On everything, it seems.
Think you can track him down?
So what's the bad news?
Huh, I'm 'er only chance. And she's my only chance. Two pawns on Rogue's board.
You're quick. For a pawn.
You know it. I lost everything. Through you.
Don't work with clan outcasts.
And there's nothin' I hate more than losin' good people to plain stupidity.
Anders Hellman. Pinpoint him for me?
Huh. Thanks.
Jumpin' too soon. First, my help's got a price. Second, and third –
Your Hellman's not on any payroll, not officially, anyway. But he does pop up in QianT's confidential stacks.
It's a Kang Tao subsidiary. Chinese corp.
Kang Tao's been using them as a fig leaf for years. Their mask for more "sensitive" operations. All that clear?
Dexter DeShawn. Jackie Welles. T-Bug.
Multiple bells ringin', V. Left a lot of bodies behind, death walks in your wake. Chalk that up to bad luck?
Theeere's the bitch I know... Ask her about 'Saka Tower. How they shot me up right in front of her.
Even to the best. To you, too, Rogue.
They're protecting him from Arasaka.
Can you track him down?
Prolly keeping him hidden from Arasaka. Must've worked on a top-secret project.
Getting a mark on him oughta be easy. Actually grabbing him – another story entirely.
Mhm – hidden from Arasaka or any other megacorp that wants what he knows.
Decrypted map of upcoming Kang Tao convoy routes.
Think Hellman might be in one of 'em? Thing is, which one?
Take a look at the specs on this one – a lone AV, no ground support. No linked cargo manifests, either.
Sure, Kang Tao sometimes transports stuff unregistered if they wanna push it under the table, but…
Catch the load on this AV. Already approved in the system, but too low. So definitely no cargo on board.
BUT there's a passenger list – Kang Tao security detail plus one VIP. Transfer from QianT.
Our boy, Hellman.
Data's all confidential. You just snap your fingers and it falls in your lap?
I know where to look. And I know whose head to put in a vise.
Bottle stays.
Gonna need a native to the area, someone who'll set up the op, cobble together the gear.
Thanks, Nix.
Think she'll help?
The Rogue I remember was one cold-ass bitch. But she usually went with her gut. Somethin' tells me she thinks you check out.
Think she'll help?
[Drink] To your health.
To your health.
To YOURS, kid. Gonna need it.
Wanna go through obits? Really?
Fine. Johnny Silverhand. Zeroed inside Arasaka Tower, before your very eyes.
Got more, if you want. Or we could just talk.
Got 'nads on you, girl. Don't like that on every woman, but they seem to suit you.
entries.maleVariant: Got balls on you, boy. Don't like that on everybody, but they seem to suit you.

entries.femaleVariant: Also, hate wastin' time. Especially answering stupid questions.
Got a shard for you – intel, interesting stuff.
Let's see what you got.
Hm. Not here, not there. Who're you?
Name's V.
And what is it you want, V?
Hope you found him.
Don't mess with 'er. She's got MR-eyes. See right through you. Give 'er the truth.
Aim to let that evaporate?
You waiting for something?
Gonna sit down?
My time's pretty valuable, V.
They're getting ready to transfer him.
Must be preppin' him for a transfer.
How would you know?
Chinese corpo playbook's an open one to me. This looks like the ol' "vanishing pigeon."
So without real firepower, I'll be able to wave to Hellman as he zips past.
Anyways... feelings be damned, I've always said. This is pure biz. You need my help, so get those eddies ready.
[Pay] This enough?
And if I don't have the cash?
Should be enough.
U-huh. And if I don't have the scratch? It's "fuck off and have a nice day"?
No. More like, "Come back when you do." Them's the breaks.
Mhm. Then, see ya. Soon.
You know where to find me.
Thanks, I'll pass.
Thanks, but I'll pass.
Good stuff. Your loss.
Be careful who you bargain with.
Make some room.
It's OK.
AV like that's a hard nut to crack.
So, a native. Know any hick mercs?
Just one. Panam Palmer.
She can't count on her clan anymore, but she's a true nomad. She knows those lands.
And she will help you. Won't have a choice.
"Won't have a choice"? Does not sound enticing – not for her, not for me.
Enticing comes at a price you can't possibly afford.
Can't possibly afford to blow this chance at nabbing Hellman.
Your operation, your call.
Even tracking that AV'll be a bitch. Familiar with the type, saw legacy models flyin' around during the war.
They're mammoth but they're quick. Plus they pack next-gen defenses. Can't take potshots at it, not even with serious firepower. Just won't work.
It's not about firepower. There are ways. And people who know them. Or who can at least improvise on a theme.
Two, please.
Got the cred for the Hellman job.
Fine.
Anders Hellman – flick me the detes.
I'm back. What about Hellman?
Hey, Rogue. I'm back. What about Hellman?
Here to see Rogue. Expectin' me.
Hey, Rogue. Got the scratch.
Need a fixer. Got somethin' that can't wait.
Need a fixer. Urgently.
Mhm. Come back tomorrow, we'll talk.
Let her in.
All these years... It's really her. Fuckin' Rogue, just kickin' it back on a couch at the Afterlife.
Matter of life and death.
Don't see that often, determination like yours. Must really need this guy.
Heh. Haven't heard that for a while, either.
Go ahead, enjoy.
[Stand] I'll do that. Thanks.
Seems wonky to me. Nomads give the city, city folk, a wide berth.
Strange. Thought nomads gave the city, and city folk, a wide berth.
[Wait]
Here to see Rogue. Got an appointment.
Hey. Got the eddies.
